'''Henri Matisse''' (Le Cateau-Cambrésis, Nord, [[Pow Frynk]], 31 Kevardhu 1869 – 3 Du 1954) o [[artyst]] a [[Pow Frynk|Bow Frynk]], godhvedhys rag y dhevnydh a [[liw]] hag y lynenieth berus ha gwredhek.

Lynednor, pryntwryer ha gravyor o ev, mes ev yw godhvedhys yn chyf avel lymner. Gwelys yw Matisse avel onen a'n artysts chyf neb a wrug gweles dhe wruthyl an displegyanjow wheldroek yn art a-varr y'n [[20ves kansblydhen|20ves cansvledhen]].<ref>[http://www.tate.org.uk/modern/exhibitions/matissepicasso/ Tate Modern: Matisse Picasso, Tate.org.uk, 2010-02-13]</ref><ref>[http://www.guardian.co.uk/culture/2002/may/07/artsfeatures Searle, Adrian, ''A momentous, tremendous exhibition'', The Guardian, De Meurth 7 Me 2002, Loundres]</ref><ref>[http://www.smithsonianmag.com/arts-culture/matisse.html Trachtman, Paul, ''Matisse & Picasso'', Smithsonian, mis Whevrel 2003]</ref><ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/4059997.stm Duchamp's urinal tops art survey, news.bbc.co.uk, 2010-12-10]</ref> 

:"Matisse a wras canfasys liwys yn spladn o arayys herwydh aga liw ha gorrys yn dyffrans a ober pyncel, ow qwandra dhort impasto tew [paynt tew] dhe gostys leven a bygment pur, traweythyow devedhys gans linen dodnek ha haval-arabesque. [Hemm o] an kensa a'n muvyanjow avant-garde (1905–7), henwys "Fauvieth" gans brusyas a art arnowyth, o cowsel a'y dhevnydh a gesunyanjow siansus a liwyow spladn hag ober pyncel nerthek rag framya an formyans".<ref name=Dabrowski/> 

Kynth o ev henwys yn kensa "Fauve" (best gwyls), warbydn an 1920s ev o gwelys moy ha moy avel mentenyor a hengov classek lymna Pow Frynk.<ref>Wattenmaker, Richard J.; Distel, Anne, et al. 1993. ''Great French paintings from the Barnes Foundation''. New York: Alfred A. Knopf. p272 ISBN 0-679-40963-7</ref>
Y vaystry a yeth semlantek a gomposter ha liw, yn obereth a wrug rewhansa moy es hantercans, a wrug gwaynya dhodho ajon avel fygur chyf yn [[art arnowyth]].<ref name=Dabrowski>[http://www.metmuseum.org/toah/hd/mati/hd_mati.htm Magdalena Dabrowski Department of Nineteenth-Century, Modern, and Contemporary Art, The Metropolitan Museum of Art Source: Henri Matisse (1869–1954) | Thematic Essay | Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History | The Metropolitan Museum of Art ] June 30, 2010</ref>

